          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Administrative Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill provides statutory authority for the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) requirement that federal agencies must submit at least one proposal for reducing direct spending before taking a discretionary administrative action that increases direct spending. Further, an agency must submit to the OMB its legal basis for concluding that a proposed administrative action is nondiscretionary and, therefore, not subject to this requirement.</p>]]>
          </text>
